cs.CC, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the construction of samplers and extractors for functions with subgaussian tails and subexponential functions, which are relevant topics in computational complexity (cs.CC), information theory (cs.IT), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the notion of randomness extractors, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
